    "last_activity_date" : 1495205230,
    "last_edit_date" : 1495541441,
    "creation_date" : 1495205230,
    "answer_id" : 44073041,
    "question_id" : 44072077,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Your XSD file that you want to validate is just an XML document that has an associated <a href=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">XSD file</a> that defines what constitutes a valid XML document.</p>\n\n<p>For details on various ways to parse an XML document with validation, see <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15732/whats-the-best-way-to-validate-an-xml-file-against-an-xsd-file\">this question</a>.</p>\n\n<p>The XML file is your XSD file. The schema file you use to validate your XML file is <a href=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema</a>.</p>\n"
  } ],
